x zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5757048\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 18, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wba1704709264749.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wba1704709264749.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wba1704709264749.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pxy1665702671817\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                           \n Setting Widget Properties in the Properties Inspector\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Properties that are set in the Properties Inspector override the default property\n    values set for the widget (if applicable) in the initialization file. At runtime, these\n    properties may be overridden by properties set in script.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__section_xtt_gtn_11c\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d801544e49\">Widget Properties of Entities and Fields</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__p_d11744e1_d11745e1_d11746e1\">For entities and fields, you edit widget properties in\n        the Entity Editor or Component Editor.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__p_d11747e1_d11748e1_d11749e1\">If you set the properties for a modeled entity or field,\n        they will be inherited in the component. If you set them in the component, the value will\n        override any value set in the modeled object or the initialization file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__p_d11750e1_d11751e1_d11752e1\">To set widget properties for entities and fields:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__ol_xm1_jtn_11c\">\n<li class=\"li\">In the Uniface IDE, open a Component or Modeled Entity for editing.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">In the Define Structure worksheet, select the entity or field. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">In the Properties Inspector, set the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Widget Type</span> appropriate to\n          the component.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">In the property <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Widget Properties</span>, click the More icon (<img alt=\"more\" class=\"image\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__image_ufk_4tn_11c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/ellipsis.png?_LANG=enus\"/>) to open a properties dialog. Each widget type will have its own set of\n          associated widget properties that you can set. For example: <div class=\"div dropDown\">\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__p_d11756e1_d11757e1_d11758e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__fig_smc_ttn_11c\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Widget Properties for Form EditBox</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"FRM Edit Box widget properties dialog\" class=\"image\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__image_tmc_ttn_11c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/widgetpropsfrmeditbox.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"div dropDown\">\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__p_d11762e1_d11763e1_d11764e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__fig_vmc_ttn_11c\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Widget Properties for Dynamic Server Page EditBox</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"DSP Edit Box widget properties dialog\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/DSP-Edit-Box-widget-properties-dialog.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 2. Widget Properties for Dynamic Server Page EditBox\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__image_axp_zmm_nhc\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/DSP-Edit-Box-widget-properties-dialog.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"div dropDown\">\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__p_d11768e1_d11769e1_d11770e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__fig_xmc_ttn_11c\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 3. </span>Widget Properties for Static Server Page Text Control</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"USP Text Control widget properties dialog\" class=\"image\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__image_ymc_ttn_11c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/widgetpropsuspeditbox.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</div></li>\n<li class=\"li\">If a widget property is not available in the Widget Properties dialog, it can be added\n          by clicking the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More</span> button and adding it as a widget\n          parameter.</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"p\">Consult the widget documentation for the valid properties and their literal property names.\n        For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qxh1718771608803.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qxh1718771608803.html\" title=\"Widgets in dynamic server pages (DSPs) determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in the client browser.\">Widget Reference: Dynamic Server Pages</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xcx1665703126648.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xcx1665703126648.html\" title=\"Uniface provides a set of HTML controls for use in static server pages (USPs).\">Widget Reference: Static Server Pages</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lov1718340866615.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lov1718340866615.html\" title=\"Widgets in Form components determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities in components running on Windows.\">Widget Reference: Forms and Reports</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__section_exb_55n_11c\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d801544e173\">Widget Properties of Components</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Dynamic and static server page components do not have widget properties (except\n          <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Title</span>), but forms have a physical widget (<code class=\"ph codeph\">uwindow</code>)\n        for which you can set the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Properties</span>, just as you would field\n        and entity widget properties.</p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__p_d11786e1_d11787e1_d11788e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__fig_sbq_gvn_11c\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 4. </span>Window Properties of Form Component</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Window Properties for From component\" class=\"image\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__image_tbq_gvn_11c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/windowpropsdialog.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__section_qjz_jq1_4cc\">\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://learn.rocketsoftware.com/course/view.php?id=507\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Learn More\" class=\"image\" id=\"pxy1665702671817__image_mwm_2m4_vdc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/My_Learn_More_Button.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/></a></p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yvs1704708821195.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Setting Properties in Initialization Files</a><p>To provide your preferred default values for many widget properties, you can define or modify logical widget definitions in the application's initialization file. These are named configurations for a variety of user interface elements, such as field widgets for desktop and web components, area frames in Form components, and entities. For more information, see Logical WidgetsLogical widgets are named configurations of physical widgets. A single physical widget may therefore have multiple logical widgets mapped to it. For fields, logical widgets provide the only way that physical widgets can be addressed. .</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/szv1704710657865.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Setting Properties in Script</a><p>You can dynamically set widget properties at runtime using ProcScript, or for dynamic server pages, in JavaScript.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5757048\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5757048\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Setting Widget Properties in the Properties Inspector Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 18, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Setting Widget Properties in the Properties Inspector Properties that are set in the Properties Inspector override the default property values set for the widget (if applicable) in the initialization file. At runtime, these properties may be overridden by properties set in script. Widget Properties of Entities and Fields For entities and fields, you edit widget properties in the Entity Editor or Component Editor. If you set the properties for a modeled entity or field, they will be inherited in the component. If you set them in the component, the value will override any value set in the modeled object or the initialization file. To set widget properties for entities and fields: In the Uniface IDE, open a Component or Modeled Entity for editing. In the Define Structure worksheet, select the entity or field. In the Properties Inspector, set the Widget Type appropriate to the component. In the property Widget Properties , click the More icon ( ) to open a properties dialog. Each widget type will have its own set of associated widget properties that you can set. For example: Figure 1. Widget Properties for Form EditBox Figure 2. Widget Properties for Dynamic Server Page EditBox Figure 3. Widget Properties for Static Server Page Text Control If a widget property is not available in the Widget Properties dialog, it can be added by clicking the More button and adding it as a widget parameter. Consult the widget documentation for the valid properties and their literal property names. For more information, see Widget Reference: Dynamic Server Pages , Widget Reference: Static Server Pages and Widget Reference: Forms and Reports . Widget Properties of Components Dynamic and static server page components do not have widget properties (except Title ), but forms have a physical widget ( uwindow ) for which you can set the Window Properties , just as you would field and entity widget properties. Figure 4. Window Properties of Form Component Related Links Setting Properties in Initialization Files To provide your preferred default values for many widget properties, you can define or modify logical widget definitions in the application's initialization file. These are named configurations for a variety of user interface elements, such as field widgets for desktop and web components, area frames in Form components, and entities. For more information, see Logical WidgetsLogical widgets are named configurations of physical widgets. A single physical widget may therefore have multiple logical widgets mapped to it. For fields, logical widgets provide the only way that physical widgets can be addressed. . Setting Properties in Script You can dynamically set widget properties at runtime using ProcScript, or for dynamic server pages, in JavaScript. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}